 (\nabla \times X)\cdot n = 0,\quad\text{and}\quad (\nabla \times X)\times n = 0. 
 \int_{V} (\nabla \times X)\cdot \nabla \phi = -\underbrace{\int_{V} \nabla \cdot (\nabla \times X)\,\phi}_{\text{This term vanishes}} + \int_S \phi\,(\nabla \times X)\cdot n\,dS.  
 \int_{V} (\nabla \times X)\cdot \nabla \phi = \underbrace{\int_{V} X \cdot \nabla \times(\nabla \phi)}_{\text{ This term vanishes}} -\int_S (X\times n)\cdot \nabla \phi\,dS. 
